Declare Variable 
DATA <varianble_name> TYPE <data_type>.  


Types of Datatypes

1.  Integers

-> i for integer    whole number.
DATA gv_count TYPE i.
gv_count = 10.

-> p for decimal    used for money.
DATA gv_price TYPE p DECIMALS 2.
gv_price = '123.45'.

-> f for float    used for scientific
DATA gv_ratio TYPE f.
gv_ratio = 3.14.


2.  Character/ Text

-> c for fixed length    length is fixed
DATA gv_code TYPE c LENGTH 3.
gv_code = 'ABC'.

->string for flexible length    Flexible length (MOST USED).
DATA gv_name TYPE string.
gv_name = 'Shubham'.


3.  Date & Time

-> d for date    Format: YYYYMMDD
DATA gv_date TYPE d.
gv_date = sy-datum.

-> t for time Format: HHMMSS
DATA gv_time TYPE t.
gv_time = sy-uzeit.


4.  Boolean (True / False)

ABAP does NOT have true/false type 
We use abap_bool.
Values:
abap_true
abap_false

DATA gv_flag TYPE abap_bool.
gv_flag = abap_true.


5.  Structure (one row)
A structure = group of different fields.

Use SAP table structure
DATA gs_flight TYPE sflight.

Now it has many fields:
gs_flight-carrid = 'LH'.


6️. Internal Table (many rows)
Table in memory.

DATA gt_flights TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sflight.

Types:
STANDARD (default)
SORTED
HASHED


7️. Reference types (advanced, just awareness)
Used for OOP.
DATA lo_obj TYPE REF TO object.


8️. Important system variables (already exist)
SAP gives you some variables automatically.

Variable	Meaning
sy-datum	Today’s date
sy-uzeit	Current time
sy-subrc	Result code
sy-uname	User name

Example:
WRITE sy-uname.


9️. Most common beginner mistake ❌

❌ Using i for money
DATA price TYPE i.   "WRONG
✅ Correct
DATA price TYPE p DECIMALS 2.


10️. Quick cheat sheet (SAVE THIS)
Type	Use
i	Counter, index
p	Price, amount
string	Text
c	Fixed codes
d	Date
t	Time
abap_bool	Yes / No
Structure	One row
Internal table	Many rows
